@Jared wrote:

ive since then updated it in the procedures, still no anti randoms though lol so basicaly its a macroer for people who are at there computer

[code]program wcer;
{.include Osi.txt}
{.include par.txt}

const
ore1 = 5009512;
ore2 = 5406848;
ore3 = 5077104;
log1 = 2117464;
words = 13553958;
waittime = 6000;

//thanks SI.SCAR************//
Function FlagPresent:boolean;
var flagimage:integer;
begin
flagimage := BitmapFromString(2, 2,‘FF00005D3311C656045D3311’);
if(findbitmapin( flagimage, x, y, 570, 5, 725, 162))then result:=true;
freebitmap(flagimage);
end;

procedure cutemdown;
var R,Rock,xf,yf: integer;
begin
R:= random(14);
case R of
0 : Rock:= ore2;
1 : Rock:= ore1;
2 : Rock:= ore3;
3 : Rock:= ore2;
4 : Rock:= ore3;
5 : Rock:= ore1;
6 : Rock:= ore2;
7 : Rock:= ore1;
8 : Rock:= ore3;
9 : Rock:= ore2;
10: Rock:= ore3;
11: Rock:= ore1;
12: Rock:= ore3;
13: Rock:= ore2;
end;
WAIT(waittime+RANDOM(846))
if(findcolorspiraltolerance(x,y,rock,1,1,517,338,5)) then
mmouse(x,y,3,3);
wait(50+random(50))
getmousepos(xf, yf);
wait(50+random(10))
if(findcolortolerance(x,y,words,1,1,517,338,40))then
mouse(xf,yf,3,3,true); writeln(‘Found tree’)
repeat
wait(200);
until(flagpresent=false);
end;

procedure dropemdown;

begin
if(invincount=28)then
dropcolor(log1);
end;

procedure runon;
begin
if(findcolor(x,y,11119017,698,469,725,498))then
mouse(x,y,3,3,true);
wait(500+random(500));
mouse(637-random(15),280-random(15),3,3, true);
wait(400+random(300))
mouse(657-random(15),198-random(15),3,3,true);
end;

begin
runon;
repeat
dropemdown;
cutemdown;
dropemdown;
until(false)
end.

[/code]
